The article discusses job creation in August, stating that job creation has picked up compared to July. Thirteen percent of businesses reported increasing employment, while 6 percent reported reducing employment. A net 20 percent of businesses plan to create new jobs. In the construction and wholesale trades industries, there are plans to increase employment, with few reductions planned. However, there is a shortage of skilled workers, which is putting pressure on compensation. Some businesses are raising compensation and providing increased training to address the shortage.